About this item

    This fits your .
  • Make sure this fits by entering your model number.
  • ﻿About Grey iPad Pencil: Pen for iPad is a light, brief stylish design with 167.4±0.5mm length, 15g weight, 2mm tip for smoothly writing and drawing. Charging for about 1.2 hours, fully charged can be used for 10-12 hours without interruption. Best Stylus for artists, teachers, and students, etc.
  • ﻿Palm Rejection and Magnetic Design: Stylus pen for iPad with palm rejection which allows you to rest your palm comfortably on the screen while using. A magnet for the iPad allows you to attach the drawing pen to the iPad side, easy to carry, and no worry about losing.
  • ﻿Smooth and Precise for iPad Pen: The 2.0mm POM tip improves accuracy and precision for a stylish pen for iPad, won't scratch the screen, no lagging, write more freely. Giving you a real creative feeling as on paper, suitable for drawing, browsing, playing games, and taking notes.
  • One Button Operation: No Bluetooth or any app connection is required for the stylist stylus pens. Simple as pressing the power button to turn on/off, responsive without delay, but pressing requires some strength, avoid power consumption due to collision when moving, and not easy to accidentally turn it off during use. If the rechargeable iPad pencil is out of power, plug in the USB cable for charging.
  • ﻿Compatible devices and Quality Assurance: Stylus pen for iPad compatible with (2018-2020) Apple iPad Pro 2nd/3rd/4th/5th (11/12.9 Inch), iPad 6th/7th/8th Gen, iPad Mini 5th Gen, iPad Air 3th/4th Gen. Product Description

The latest stylus pen for the iPad is more suitable for your work, life, and entertainment.


AZX aims to design a stylus engineered like a computer, works like a pencil, focuses on providing the user with a smooth and natural writing experience, and provides super technical support and after-sales service, strives to make every customer 100% satisfied, to be the best stylus supplier.

AZX Pencil for iPad

Note

Not work for iPhone, Android, Microsoft devices, iPad Pro 1st&2nd, iPad pro 10.5", iPad pro 9.7", earlier versions of iPad. Please update your iOS to the 12.2 version or above.

If the stylus or finger cannot write, please set your iPad or iPad Pro as follows:

a.Settings--->Apple Pencil--->Turn off the Apple pencil.

b.Settings---> Notes--->Turn off ‘Only Draw with Apple Pencil’.

Warming Tips:

  • Please ensure it has enough power before use.
  • Don’t use it while your iPad is charging, that may cause a skip.
  • Cannot be used for switching apps.
  • Highly recommend using with screen protector together.

          Color: whiteVine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
          This is my first experience using a pencil with my iPad Pro, so I don’t have anything to compare this to, but so far I’m very pleased.

          The pencil came neatly packaged and includes a couple of replacement tips and a charging cable. It is well made, and it’s comfortable to write with. I appreciate that it connects magnetically to my iPad Pro, and that it charges with USB-C (same as my iPad Pro).

          Obviously this is not as advanced as the Apple Pencil, but it’s a fraction of the cost and meets my needs as a college student for note taking and studying.

          If you’re looking for an affordable alternative to the Apple Pencil this is a good option.
